query: how to enhance the productivity of millet crop
response: To enhance the productivity of millet crops, you can consider establishing diverse seed centers for easy access to quality seeds, implementing improved agronomic practices, utilizing appropriate farm mechanization through custom hiring centers, provide training to farmers through community resource persons, and promoting millets in urban and small towns. As for improving the harvesting of millets, it is recommended to wait until the ears turn yellowish-brown before harvesting, heap the harvested ears and cover them with ragi straw for 2-3 days before threshing, and separate grains are winnowed and cleaned. Farmers can also utilize ragi threshers developed by OUAT, which are both power and bullock operated to improve grain quality and save time.

query: How can farmers apply to government schemes in Odisha?
response: Farmers in Odisha can apply to government schemes through the Sugam portal, which is a single window platform for farmers and agri-preneurs. The portal digitizes all farmer-centric schemes and services of the Fisheries & Animal Resource Development (F&ARD) department and the Department of Agriculture & Farmer Empowerment (DAFE), Government of Odisha. The portal provides relevant information such as guidelines and eligibility criteria for all schemes, and applicants can track the real-time status of their applications on the portal or the app using their mobile number. Additionally, applicants get notifications on SMS or E-mail as their application is approved or rejected at each stage. The portal also streamlines the application process and makes it a single window for the farmers.

query: Tell me something about treatment of termites in sugarcane?
response: To control termites in sugarcane, you can spray Bifenthrin @ 30 ml or Fipronil @ 15ml Chloropyriphos @30 ml in 15 liter of water. Termites attack setts, shoots, canes and also stubbles. They gain entry through the cut ends or through buds of the setts and feed on the soft tissues. The tunnel excavated is filled with soil, which affects germination and ultimately the cane yield.

query: How can farmers apply to government schemes in Odisha?
response:
Farmers in Odisha can apply to government schemes through the Sugam portal, which is India's first-ever single window platform for farmers and agri-preneurs. Here are the features of the Sugam Portal:

- Online Application: Farmer-facing web portal and mobile app for application of all schemes and services in the agriculture and allied sector.
- Status Tracking: Applicants can track the real-time status of their applications on the portal or the app using their mobile number.
- Proactive Status Notification: Applicants also get notifications on SMS or E-mail as their application is approved or rejected at each stage.
- Single Window Service: Necessary service applications from different government departments such as water supply and electricity connection have been integrated with the platform thereby streamlining the application process and making it a single window for the farmers.
- Online Application Processing: End-to-end processing of applications including uploading of verification reports and geo-tagged photographs is enabled online on the web portal and mobile app for block, district, and state-level officers.
- Reports & Dashboards: Scheme-wise reports and dashboards for department officials to track application pendency status and delivery performance in respective jurisdictions.

All farmer-centric schemes and services of the Fisheries & Animal Resource Development (F&ARD) department and the Department of Agriculture & Farmer Empowerment (DAFE), Government of Odisha are digitized on the Sugam Portal.
